    <h1 style="text-align: center; color: rgb(19, 160, 7);">TEA </h1>
    <p style="text-align: center;">A beverage produced by steeping in freshly boiled water the young leaves and leaf buds of the tea plant, Camellia sinensis.</p>
    <br><br>

    <div class="div-container">
        <ul class="nav nav-tabs">
            <li class="active"><a data-toggle="tab" href="#tea1">Green Tea</a></li>
            <li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#tea2">Lemon Tea</a></li>
            <li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#tea3">Ginger Tea</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="tab-content">
        <div id="tea1" class="tab-pane fade in active">
            <h2 style="text-align: center; color: rgb(19, 160, 7);"> GREEN TEA</h2>
            <div class="DivTea">

                <img src="https://media.istockphoto.com/photos/tea-picture-id1135520405?k=20&m=1135520405&s=612x612&w=0&h=1fnHwNIAyPxtnIxCw7yH2vyTozWXAdWCInQ2AMvOMzg=" alt="Green Tea" width="486px" height="385px" opacity="0.7">

            </div>
            <br>
            <p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: rgb(19, 160, 7);">Green Tea</span> is brewed from dried leaves of Camellia sinensis but it should be unoxidized to preserve antioxidants. </p>
        </div>
        <div id="tea2" class="tab-pane fade">
            <h2 style="text-align: center; color: rgb(212, 209, 21);"> LEMON TEA</h2>
            <div class="DivTea">

                <img src="https://www.whiskaffair.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Lemon-Tea-4.jpg" alt="Lemon Tea" width="486px" height="385px" opacity="0.7">

            </div>
            <br>
            <p style="text-align: center;">Prepared from Black Tea or Green Tea, <span style="color: rgb(151, 149, 16);">Lemon Tea</span> is a hot drink added with the right amount of lemon juice. The amount is based from the person's preference. </p>
        </div>
        <div id="tea3" class="tab-pane fade">
            <h2 style="text-align: center; color: rgb(202, 168, 13);"> GINGER TEA</h2>
            <div class="DivTea">

                <img src="https://health.clevelandclinic.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/10/gingerTeaBenefits-656808066_770x533.jpg" alt="Ginger Tea" width="486px" height="385px" opacity="0.7">

            </div>
            <br>
            <p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: rgb(202, 168, 13);">Ginger Tea</span> has a sweet spicy flavour coming from the roots of a Ginger plant. Mostly prepared by steeping the ginger in hot water to extract flavour.</p>
        </div>

    </div>
